	<tr>
		
			<td colspan="2" bgcolor="#DEDACB" background="http://www.everlore.com/gimages/tb_beige.gif">
		
				<font face="verdana" size="2" color="black">
				ok this should help people decide which DD spell is better at this level (i did a bitta homework);<BR>
with 133 int at level 8 with my gnome mag i have 228.8 mana:<BR>
-Shock of blades-<BR>
 7 casts<BR>
 217 dammage<BR>
 15 sec (not counting repop time on the spells but since this has no extra repop it shouldn't change much)<BR>
 18.6 mana left over<BR>
-Flame Bolt-<BR>
 5 casts<BR>
 205 dammage<BR>
 13 sec (also not considering repop)<BR>
 28.8 mana left over<BR>
<BR>
-Conclusion-<BR>
these spells are pretty evenly matched... the shock does more dammage but takes 2 sec more... <BR>
the flame bolt which has a longer cast time by .4 seconds in the long run takes less time but does 12 less dammage and leaves you with about 10 more mana.<BR>
if the creatures you are fighting don't resist often (and because i have a jr. apprentice robe with +1 mana) it's perfectly set so that i can cast the 5 flame bolts and have exactly 29.8 mana left over... this means i have to wait one second and should be able to cast a shock of blades bringing the dammage up to 236 dammage in 14 seconds as opposed to 217 in 15 seconds.  <BR>
<BR>
origionally i figured the shock spell would win the battle because VI likes ta make the less dammage spells better i found that flame bolt would be the logical choice with one cast of shock at the end.<BR>
<BR>
<BR>
-Another way-<BR>
there's another way ta look at it too:<BR>
flame bolt gets resisted easily... i have casted flame bolt and done 8 dammage before wow what a waste of 40 mana that's .2 dammage per one mana point... really inefficent  unless you can find out the statistics on a creature resisting a both of these spells and by how much they resist it, it is impossible to calculate which combo is ACTUALLY better.<BR>
the flame bolt does more dammage (with one shock at the end of the string) faster<BR>
but the drawbacks are: LOS (line of sight), and resist<BR>
<BR>
Shock of blades does less dammage (if you shock at the end of the bolts... again i gotta mention that) in a longer time... but is harder to resist and is not LOS<BR>
<BR>
you decide!<BR>
<BR>
Xaban<BR>
8 Mag Innoruuk<BR>
<BR>
Fayzn<BR>
31 Cleric Innoruuk<BR>
 <BR>
Fayden<BR>
22 Mag Innoruuk (yes i do have 2 mag's)
