	<tr>
		
			<td colspan="2" bgcolor="#DEDACB" background="http://www.everlore.com/gimages/tb_beige.gif">
		
				<font face="verdana" size="2" color="black">
				Shock of blades, magician spell level 8<BR>
<BR>
Supposedly you summon blades that shock the target. Yes, the spell uses CONJURATION (!!!).<BR>
<BR>
It does 31dmg , +1 each level. Usually full dmg.<BR>
Stuns target, although I've never really noticed if that helps alot, dunno about interrupting spells. I guess it is hard to resist, because from level 8 to level 11 I have only had 1 resist.. And boy have I cast it alot. It takes about half a bubble of mana (30), (I have 117int, level 11).<BR>
<BR>
<BR>
SHOCK OF BLADES  VS  FIRE BOLT<BR>
Lets say you're level 12<BR>
<BR>
Shock of Blades: 30 mana, 35 damage<BR>
Fire Bolt: 40 mana, 45 damage<BR>
<BR>
For a 120 mana, you cast Blades 4 times and Bolt 3 times:<BR>
<BR>
Shock of Blades: 35dmg * 4 =  140 dmg<BR>
Fire Bolt: 45 dmg * 3 = 135 dmg<BR>
<BR>
For Blades you get about 1.166 points of damage per point of mana.<BR>
For Bolt you get 1.125, diffrence of about <BR>
0,041 damage<BR>
<BR>
NOTE that at lower levels, like 8 for example, the spells do 31 and 41, so the diffrence is slighter, even though its pretty slight already at level 12. I dont believe the damage goes higher that 35 and 45.<BR>
<BR>
Other stuff:<BR>
Bolt: very long range, more damage per cast.<BR>
Blades: low resist, fast cast, stun, line of sight not req.<BR>
<BR>
Overall, Shock of Blades is not a bad DD (direct damage) spell. I don't know if Fire Bolt can be called a DD since it isnt Direct damage but a bolt that needs to reach the target first. I don't have an opinion on which one is best, but I find myself using to Shock of Blades nearly all the time, and I've become used to it and its red flash and its rumbling boom sound.<BR>
<BR>
Groktar<BR>
11 magician<BR>
PREXUS<BR>

				</font>
			</td>

	</tr>
	
