				Llail, you probably have already figured this out but for other people just reaching this level here it goes.<BR>
<BR>
The Fire Bolt Spell has an incredibly long range.  Basically if you can see it on your screen you are within range of your bolt.  Also as you pointed out it does more damage.  The down side is it has a slower casting time and is line of sight, so your pet and other players can block this spell.  Also at first you will have a lot of trouble hitting mobs up or down hill from you with this spell.<BR>
<BR>
The shock of blades has a rather short range, but a very fast casting time (apx 2.4 secs) and does not require line of sight.  Meaning my pet or another player can be in between me and the Mob and I will still hit the mob.  Also Hills, are not a problem.  Finally the shock spell interrupts spell casting so is great to use against magical mobs and in PVP.<BR>
<BR>
I use both spells all the time.  I usually use the flame bolt to start a fight and then use Shock of blades as the fight continues.  <BR>
<BR>
After buying your primary pet spell I would say this is the second most important level 8 spell there is.<BR>
<BR>
My personal rankings for level 8 spells are:<BR>
<BR>
1  Solo Pet (I prefer water, most prefer Earth)<BR>
2  Shock of Blades<BR>
3  Fire Shield<BR>
4  Renew Elements<BR>
5  Group Pet (I like Fire here)<BR>
6  Lesser Shielding<BR>
7  Invisibility<BR>
8  Flame Bolt<BR>
9  Pet 3<BR>
10 Pet 4<BR>
11 Dimensional Pocket<BR>
12 Staff of Tracing<BR>
13 Eye of Zomm
				</font>
			</td>

	</tr>
	
